Address: 128 Grantville Glen Alvie Road Grantville VIC 3984
Description:
Prime entry level home in a peaceful location.
Tucked away from the road in a quiet neighbourhood, this three-bedroom home on 564m2 (approx.) is just one minute away from the Grantville shopping precinct and presents a fantastic opportunity to enter the property market. With glimpses of the bay from the bedroom, one could easily imagine the magnificent views from an additional level or you may prefer to enjoy the home just as it is.
Light and homely, this charming property features three bedrooms with wall to wall carpets, two of which have built in robes. The master bedroom has a separate entry to the verandah with glass sliding doors to allow fresh air to circulate on those warm summer nights. The spacious open plan living/dining/kitchen is a welcoming space for friends and family to gather and other features include a central bathroom with bath, large laundry, separate toilet, linen closet and inverter split system. Outside is a carport with plenty of additional off road parking and a large backyard.
Offering so much potential in an area famous for its fishing, boating, wineries and epicurean delights, this home is also central to coastal and bushland reserves while being only 1:20hr away from Melbourne. Within half an hour in the other direction, you'll reach Phillip Island or enjoy a scenic drive along the Bass Coast. There is so much to see and do in this beautiful part of the world.
Offering
• Open plan living, dining and spacious kitchen
• Three carpeted bedrooms, two with built in robes
• Master bedroom with its own separate entry
• Inverter split system heating/cooling
• Carport with additional off road parking
• Large backyard, paved area with seating

Address: 49 Ten Chain Road French Island VIC 3921
Description:
THE GOOD OIL
If city-life is giving you the pip, you need never pay another council rate or power bill by escaping to this, your very own 40 acre hideaway, fully off grid yet only 1.5hrs from Melbourne, with no council rates, no power companies and no water rates!
Imagine sitting on your island verandah, overlooking the bay, enjoying olives grown from your own olive grove, whilst dipping bread into your freshly pressed olive oil and taking in the scenery of llamas, alpacas, Clydesdale Horses and even koalas in the surrounding native trees. There's also an abundance of birdlife, with no foxes or possums to upset the applecart!
The home is an absolute Aussie Gem comprising 3 bedrooms, wrap-around verandahs, a large kitchen, a composting toilet and grey water management system. This peaceful haven also boasts established fruit orchard, vegie garden, chooks, worm farm, its own solar and wind power, battery storage, solar hot water, ample firewood for the wood heater (with wet back to support solar hot water), over 70,000 litres of rainwater tank storage, ample machinery shedding and a timber barn.
This established lifestyle property with income and opportunities for further diversification, is entirely NASAA certified organic and currently home to French Island Olives, including a grove of 800 mature olive trees, supported with all equipment on site, such as an oil processor in a dedicated facility on the property. The remaining property is divided into 7 grazing paddocks all with natural shelter offering opportunities for a small grazing business.
For more information, including a comprehensive list of plant and equipment, or to arrange a private inspection, please call local agent Philip Bock on 0438 497 715.

Description:
FRENCH ISLAND FARM ON 180 ACRES!
Established in 1905, DE LA HAYE PARK is the largest cattle farm on Coast Road, French Island, comprising paddocks, dams, cattle yards, machinery, shedding and a 5+ bedroom dwelling overlooking your own wetland-lake, providing home to an abundance of wildlife and birds including Swans, Ducks, Ibis, Kookaburras and Parrots.
De La Haye Park is the perfect island lifestyle farming property, suitable for cattle, sheep, horses or a multitude of other opportunities, with enough space to accommodate multiple families and only 10 km from the French Island passenger ferry jetty.
If you are ready for a sea-change/tree-change, come to unique French Island for a look around and let your future thrive.
French Island is approximately two thirds national park and is unincorporated, therefore is not governed by a local council, so no council rates apply. Being off the grid, means there are no power companies to deal with and no water rates to pay. About an hour from Melbourne, but like stepping back in time, we are a small community of around 100 residents, accessible by passenger ferry from Stony Point, or vehicle barge from Corinella.
Contact French Islands local representative Phil Bock on 5980 1234 to discuss this unique opportunity.

Description:
The Horseshoe Homestead - your next project?
Originally built at the beginning of last century, the former De La Haye farm house along Coast Road just north of Tankerton on French Island has been abandoned since the early 1970's but its' foot thick concrete, daub and timber walls are still standing, defying the elements and hoping that one day someone, possibly inspired by television programs such as Restoration Home and Country House Rescue, will come along and resuscitate what is left of the whimsically named "Horseshoe Homestead" presumably after the shape of the original building.
Consisting of three main rooms to front with a fire place and chimney at one end and a double internal brick fire place between the other two main rooms inside, the still partially roofed building boasts several dormer windows in the roofline, a unique architectural feature for the time, which still lets filtered light into the roof space with its original timber pole rafters.
The back of the building has collapsed but there is still plenty to indicate the wealth that was once generated by the industrious rural production of the property in years gone by such as the well about 10 meters from the house and the remains of a Chicory Kiln on a nearby property.
A welcoming stand of mature deciduous trees with their carpet of jonquils surround the house and presents an image of solid permanency from the front gate; but the house is not the only desirable feature. The property is an elevated 120 Acres close to the coast, well fenced and divided into 4 paddocks with a good sized dam in each. There are half a dozen stands of mature shelter trees, a 4 bay machine shed and another smaller shed for storage. Currently used by a neighbouring farmer for grazing purposes, the arrangement works well, as the grass is kept down and the cows are happy. As this a farming property there is no GST on the sale.
Live the lifestyle of the weekend farmer at an affordable price. Contact Phil Bock our resident French Island representative on 0438 497 715. Phil will meet you at the ferry and take you directly to the property which is only 9 kms away.
